      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>1119</offset>
        <text>In our simulations, glacioeustatic sea-level fall associated with the growth of Antarctic ice sheets permanently reduces global calcium carbonate accumulation on the continental shelves, leading to an increase in pelagic burial via permanent deepening of the calcite compensation depth.
</text>
